Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.19,0:00:04.35,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave the solids to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.35,0:00:05.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:10.73,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki's moving tomorrow, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.32,0:00:13.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We have three days to bring in the finished manuscript. {Was: We've got three days to get the finishing touches on the manuscript done and bring it in.} {Timing Note: Too long. Something shorter would be better.}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.86,0:00:17.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We must use all the time we have to make it even a little better.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.29,0:00:22.24,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll do my best on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.62,0:00:25.20,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.71,0:00:29.50,Main,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1200)}I'll wait forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.97,0:02:03.22,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.22,0:02:04.43,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.43,0:02:06.81,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably someone selling newspapers or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:09.21,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro! Takagi! 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.21,0:02:10.47,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're there, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.52,0:02:11.52,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's Miyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:12.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:14.02,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.02,0:02:17.05,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,When she finds out later that I was here, she'll beat the crap out of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:18.80,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Mashiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.32,0:02:20.36,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He's drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:23.24,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We've got our deadline in three days, so don't bother him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:24.57,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.62,0:02:26.29,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:26.95,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Miyoshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:28.83,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro...{\alpha&HFF&} kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.83,0:02:29.62,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro... kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.62,0:02:30.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:32.96,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell Miho your email address?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.96,0:02:33.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.34,0:02:35.84,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:39.44,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I know hers, but she still doesn't know mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.84,0:02:42.93,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you email her at least once, she won't know, will she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.93,0:02:47.35,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,So even though you met with her after graduation, you didn't tell her?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:50.01,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking about stuff like email addresses then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.44,0:02:53.69,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We both only said one sentence to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:54.91,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,One sentence?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.86,0:02:57.11,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.11,0:02:57.90,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not telling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.57,0:03:01.55,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Well fine, but you need to tell her your email.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.16,0:03:04.13,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,She can't even email you to say she's moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:06.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I know that because you told me, Miyoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:09.33,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't tell her I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.33,0:03:11.54,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, send an email her at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:14.08,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.17,0:03:19.03,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want the first email I send her to be random like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:24.03,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I do think it would be better to do it sooner, but I need to finish the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:27.41,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,So I can't email her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.02,0:03:30.25,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.93,0:03:34.02,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Then go ahead and say that I told you she's moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.02,0:03:37.94,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm sure she'll send you a very nice email in reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.28,0:03:41.22,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,All right, work hard, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:46.19,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Miyoshi sure is a good person deep down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:47.24,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.66,0:03:51.36,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we must get this done by the deadline!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:04:00.05,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess the younger they are, the faster they progress.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:02.47,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, that's not the only reason for this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:05.84,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's like they put their souls into this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.51,0:04:09.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.27,0:04:15.44,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I can really feel your desire to win against Niizuma-kun in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:18.36,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,This is an amazing manuscript. You did really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:20.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.82,0:04:24.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally done... Now I can email Azuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:26.99,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Want to go get something good to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:29.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, no. I'll be okay for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:33.00,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I pulled two all-nighters, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:33.83,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.33,0:04:35.91,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:39.24,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You two do look tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.36,0:04:44.05,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then all there's left is to think of the comment to put in on the last page.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.05,0:04:49.30,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,"We worked really hard to draw this, and we would be delighted to hear your impressions" is fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.30,0:04:50.26,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:51.52,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:54.23,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, do you two have bank accounts?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:57.85,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.85,0:04:59.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.48,0:05:03.38,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Your payment for the manuscript is given via a bank deposit, so make one by June.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:08.74,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I hate to ask, but how much is our manuscript payment?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:10.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew he'd ask.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.66,0:05:13.45,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Newcomers all get 9000 yen a page.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.37,0:05:16.21,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's definitely calculating that right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:21.04,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Now all that's left is the questionnaire results.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:23.80,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-san assessment was good, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.80,0:05:24.72,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like we can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:29.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.64,0:05:31.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:33.53,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"See you later"{\i0} ?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.31,0:05:38.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"This is Mashiro. Good evening."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.64,0:05:41.86,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe "Good evening, this is Mashiro" would be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.54,0:05:43.52,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,The greeting should be first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:49.52,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't need this sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:54.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I should apologize for writing those weird things to her in class that made her cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:58.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and also for not sending her chocolate on White Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:58.87,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL note: White Day takes place on March 14th when boys send chocolate to girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.04,0:06:04.25,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Also, sorry for not saying much on our graduation day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:09.96,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of all just apologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.97,0:06:17.91,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,O–Okay... Now to tell her about us running in NEXT! and the day it goes on sale...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.11,0:06:23.77,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I can't type anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:24.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.40,0:06:25.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Character limit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:27.24,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,True, 5000 characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.24,0:06:28.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No way, I've already typed that much?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:32.32,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,A–Anyway, I have to read over what I've written so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:38.55,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I've looked over it again and again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.25,0:06:42.03,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's already 9AM... Well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.37,0:06:43.54,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:52.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, guess I'll go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,An email?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:01.81,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki?! So fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:03.47,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So short!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:06.57,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really happy she replied, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.57,0:07:08.81,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,compared to my 5000-character long one...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.24,0:07:11.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll just send one in a sort of joking way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.74,0:07:16.22,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"Azuki-san, isn't your email a little short?" {It's also written onscreen. I think it's funny to put the face in the sub, but you don't need to do that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:23.31,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"We can finally email each other, so shouldn't we talk to each other more?" {Removed smilies because ^ became arrows}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.91,0:07:25.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Send.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.85,0:07:28.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Time for bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.63,0:07:32.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Another fast one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:37.78,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"Meh"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.18,0:07:42.02,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,That's so cute... She had this kind of side?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:43.73,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And it's still so short.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.77,0:07:47.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But Azuki's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:54.70,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.70,0:07:55.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shuujin...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.41,0:07:58.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,in case we get first place in the questionnaires,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:01.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,start thinking about making a serialization name for "Kane to Chie".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.71,0:08:03.83,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have time to play around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.83,0:08:04.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:05.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Understand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:08.32,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that authoritative tone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:11.17,Main,Aida,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.17,0:08:11.74,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.17,0:08:16.30,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,This Takagi-Mashiro team has gotten way better from the name stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:18.08,Main,Kimu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I really thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.14,0:08:20.10,Main,Kimu,0000,0000,0000,,This thing's really interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:21.68,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:24.98,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Even the ever-scathing Aida-san... {removed "likes it"--he never said it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:28.48,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Editor-in-Chiefs Yahagi-san and Heishi-san both gave good assessments.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:31.69,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,This really could beat Niizuma-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:34.86,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,That will never become wide-reaching popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:37.63,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way Niizuma Eiji will lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.45,0:08:41.05,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi, Mashiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:43.41,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,You two are in the same class!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:44.92,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Miyoshi, you showed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.92,0:08:45.53,Main,Miyoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:49.95,Main,Miyoshi,0000,0000,0000,,You're in class 1 with Suzuki and Saitou from Ake-middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:52.62,Main,Miyoshi,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I the only one in class 3?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.37,0:08:54.47,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:57.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Saikou, do you think we should have a penname?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.18,0:09:00.22,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a pain if this gets out in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.22,0:09:01.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Like what happened with Ishizawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:03.68,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.81,0:09:09.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine with it if you are, but will we make it in time for {\i1}NEXT!{\i0} ? {Italicized to kill the awkward !? . Line split? Y/N?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:11.08,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I'll email Hattori-san and ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:19.81,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,He said if we do it today, we can make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.95,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Then could you think of one during the entrance ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:24.50,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Me too, me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:27.79,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. We don't need you to think about it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.79,0:09:28.79,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hit me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.79,0:09:30.06,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't going to!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.30,0:09:35.91,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I think it would be best to make it a blend of our names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:38.26,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Maki Morito or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.26,0:09:40.93,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess then no one would figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.66,0:09:43.97,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.97,0:09:45.01,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Ashiro Muto.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.60,0:09:48.90,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,"So Miho and Mashiro's dream comes true."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.97,0:09:48.90,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL note: The name is made up of the kanjis of: "A" from "Azuki", "shiro" from "Mashiro", "mu" meaning "dream" and "to" meaning "come true".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:50.38,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Miho would love this, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.81,0:09:52.94,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I not in it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:54.69,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not in it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:57.65,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have anything to do with it, I'm an author!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.65,0:09:58.74,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:02.09,TL Notes,TL Note,0000,0000,0000,,TL note: Now, added, is the kanji for "gi" from "Takagi".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:02.09,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi Muto.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:03.83,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Mashrio?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:07.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's kind of cliché, and sort of embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.79,0:10:09.67,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.67,0:10:12.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uhh, I don't really care, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:13.63,Main,Kaya,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:17.55,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good. I'll contact Hattori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.55,0:10:18.49,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:22.13,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is good.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.51,0:10:26.67,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This really might make Azuki happy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.90,0:10:28.69,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, send!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.30,0:10:34.16,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,That was fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:40.07,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}Let's make our dream come true, just like your pen name says.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.28,0:10:42.37,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.07,0:10:44.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Just like I thought, Azuki also...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:46.91,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:49.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's really short again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:57.17,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,This is a sample issue I just got.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:10:59.09,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.13,0:11:01.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Ours is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.93,0:11:02.76,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:04.35,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:06.68,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's a real manga now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:08.18,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.28,0:11:21.24,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma Eiji's CROW.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.41,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It really {\i1}is{\i0} good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:25.70,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Its sense of speed and intensity makes you want to read it all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.12,0:11:29.79,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I read ours countless times since it had become a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.79,0:11:32.54,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't know if it's interesting or not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.54,0:11:34.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,No, ours is more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:39.55,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You're really confident, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:41.11,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.91,0:11:43.89,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's just my personal opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:46.26,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,but I felt like ours was a more interesting read.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.26,0:11:47.18,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.60,0:11:50.93,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'll win, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:56.61,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The story Takagi-kun wrote matches perfectly with the drawings Mashiro-kun drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:11:58.94,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,They draw out each other's good points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.57,0:12:02.07,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,That's my number one reason for thinking you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:03.76,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:07.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,But, Niizuma-san's story and drawing go well together too, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.78,0:12:08.38,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:12.71,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,both Niizuma-kun's artwork and story are far from a newcomer's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.71,0:12:13.58,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Especially the artwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:16.38,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But this can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:19.03,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,He's already been drawing for ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.64,0:12:23.55,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But Niizuma-kun will split votes with the other battle manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.55,0:12:25.34,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Ours doesn't have any works that overlap it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:25.87,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:30.49,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that if we went one-on-one with him, we would lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.09,0:12:34.48,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,A magazine will always have lots of works running in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.48,0:12:37.41,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't think this is a bad way to operate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.01,0:12:39.02,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,More than anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:43.44,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,the most important factor for success in Jack is the questionnaire results.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.15,0:12:45.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Questionnaires...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.36,0:12:51.10,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jack's manga are ranked every week according to these questionnaire postcards.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:52.87,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a serious battle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:56.93,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just like boxers standing in the ring every week.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:13:01.71,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}These questionnaires have me swinging back and forth between happiness and worry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:05.13,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've taken every place from second to twentieth, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:07.34,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've never once been first.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:11.11,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would really like to get first, even if it's just once.{\i0} {QC: Shorten?}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:16.22,Main,Kawaguchi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\fad(0,600)}That's a dream I've had ever since I got serialized.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.91,0:13:20.77,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,When do the questionnaire results come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.77,0:13:23.34,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,There are two; the {\i1}early report{\i0} and the {\i1}real deal{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:27.45,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The early report is a hand-counted total of a hundred cards that came early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:30.20,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,For the main magazine, they comes out on Tuesdays, the day after it goes on sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.32,0:13:33.12,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The real deal comes out of a lot more that arrive...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.12,0:13:36.33,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,by putting a thousand randomly selected cards in a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:39.50,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,It gives us in detail which got the "number one most interesting" votes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.50,0:13:41.63,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,which got "second most" and "third most" votes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.37,0:13:44.42,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,what averages ages for whom sent them in,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:46.09,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,and the ranking and gender ratio for each age.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.09,0:13:48.51,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,That comes out on Friday for the main magazine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.51,0:13:54.00,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,but for NEXT! it's around two weeks after it goes on sale. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.83,0:13:56.73,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}early report{\i0} and the{\i1} real deal{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.73,0:13:58.39,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So it happens twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:00.48,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,To be precise, we take them one more time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:03.57,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,but we only tell the authors up to the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.57,0:14:06.43,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,So... would you like me to tell you the early report, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:08.61,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The real deal counts for everything, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.61,0:14:10.03,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,If the real deal is everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:13.33,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,then hearing the early report doesn't have much of a meaning, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:16.58,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,We have the early report so authors can get their readers impressions in a chart...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:20.50,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and find out what they want for what comes next in their story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.54,0:14:24.30,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,There are some that don't want to hear the real deal or the early report.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.49,0:14:26.59,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,They say, "Only tell me when I'm in first."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:29.25,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So even if we don't hear the early report...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:32.18,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm a little curious about both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:34.93,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.93,0:14:36.86,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.52,0:14:39.56,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure we can do it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:41.08,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I said before,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.15,0:14:44.27,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,we don't know for certain what will be popular, beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.82,0:14:49.26,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,So you should be prepared for any kind of results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.92,0:14:50.81,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:53.11,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's still quite a while before the results come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.57,0:14:56.44,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,The best thing you can do is think about your next work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:14:57.91,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:00.49,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I'll contact you when we get the early report.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.22,0:15:04.39,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Questionnaires, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:08.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's really put a damper on my excitement of running in NEXT!.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.09,0:15:10.80,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think we can win, so—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.80,0:15:11.05,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:14.30,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,We can be serialized while we're going to high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.18,0:15:18.46,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,I can finish the names, but what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.15,0:15:20.70,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,If it means getting serialized, I'll do if even if it kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.91,0:15:26.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we get first, I don't think Hattori-san will try to serialize {\i1}Kane to Chie{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.45,0:15:30.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, he did say "next work".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:33.87,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It's normal to get serialized after getting first in NEXT!.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:36.86,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Even more so if it's a first pushing down Eiji who's already basically been chosen for serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:43.04,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But Hattori-san won't leave the idea of us only getting serialized once we're out of high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.81,0:15:45.85,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,However, if we take first place...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:55.22,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,and make a name for serialization that Hattori-san approves of...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:57.39,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.39,0:15:58.88,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, he would consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:03.10,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And if he's still reluctant, we can talk it out with people above him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:03.96,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Saikou...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.56,0:16:07.19,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Our goal is to have an anime adaptation by eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:08.76,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We have to do that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.15,0:16:15.45,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It would be all right to have chapter one overlap with what runs in NEXT!, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:18.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head back and get started on it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.83,0:16:21.73,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:45.50,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,"In the end this world is money! Smart people win using the power of money!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.90,0:16:48.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that's so cruel to end it with that line!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:49.21,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,This is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:53.11,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That finishes off chapter one's fifty-one pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:16:59.11,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's an email from Azuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.33,0:17:01.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.17,0:17:08.42,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.42,0:17:11.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,She really makes sure to send an email whenever something happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.76,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,So today was the day NEXT! goes on sale?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:15.63,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.02,0:17:17.51,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We sure are incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.51,0:17:20.22,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,We got so wrapped up in our name that we forgot about the release date.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.22,0:17:22.56,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki said it stood out in NEXT!.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.12,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Azuki-san. She has a good eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:27.48,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to reply with "Thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.63,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, let's get going on chapter two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:32.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.16,0:17:35.15,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,He's actually swimming in all the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.15,0:17:36.70,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this going a little too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:40.99,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. In chapter three all that money gets taken from him. {Damn you, spoilers!}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:43.70,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:45.30,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the early report?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:47.95,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? This is Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.13,0:17:49.78,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.19,0:17:53.42,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,For the early report, we're first!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:17:54.49,Main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,YES!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.92,0:17:56.63,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But don't get relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.63,0:17:58.55,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You two have thirty-three votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:18:00.46,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun has thirty-one votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.93,0:18:02.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,A difference of two votes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.64,0:18:04.77,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility he'll overtake you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:07.04,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Below that is twenty-six... nineteen...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:12.81,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Hattori guy...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.78,0:18:16.39,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Eiji loses, it will put a damper on our serialization.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.14,0:18:20.11,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, there's no way Niizuma Eiji will lose.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.11,0:18:21.85,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The real deal will definitely be in our favor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:36.26,Main,Kimu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... if this keeps up and you get first, is {\i1}Kono Yo wa Kane to Chie{\i0} going to head for serialization?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:38.33,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.80,0:18:40.72,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we get first place in NEXT!...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.72,0:18:42.46,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please think about us moving toward serialization.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:46.85,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,No, they have still only entered high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:50.48,Main,Kimu,0000,0000,0000,,But the authors probably really want to, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:52.08,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,They sure do...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:54.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:56.65,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,So should we call Hattori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:58.02,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him we finished a new name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:00.49,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell him they're serialization names for {\i1}Kane to Chie{\i0} yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:01.64,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:04.65,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You want to surprise Hattori-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:13.63,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.63,0:19:14.33,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.13,0:19:16.25,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:18.95,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,First, I just got the results for the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.16,0:19:21.45,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Your rank for the real deal is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:26.39,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Third place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.48,0:19:28.60,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Third?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.83,0:19:30.98,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate you didn't get first, but
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:33.10,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,third place for your first appearance in print is quite good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.10,0:19:36.02,Up of Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,First place is Niizuma Eiji-kun with 503 votes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.02,0:19:38.03,Up of Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Below that was 312 votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.03,0:19:40.36,Up of Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You two had 308 votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:45.25,Up of Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,2000)}In other words, you got proportionately the same as in the early report, but Niizuma-kun and the others increased. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:37.40,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We lost...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:38.65,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to Niizuma Eiji...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.32,0:19:41.82,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No... even more than Eiji...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:48.63,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma-kun, you got first place in the questionnaires.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.70,0:19:49.70,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.70,0:19:53.00,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,What are questionnaires?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:57.04,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,When you ran your work for the Tezuka Award, I told you that you placed second, didn't I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.04,0:20:00.51,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I probably just said "Okay" because I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.34,0:20:05.51,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I think I can make the character designs for serialization even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:07.90,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,I can probably go with this protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.51,0:20:10.22,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is fine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.56,0:20:14.10,Main,Yuujirou,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This boy doesn't need to know about the questionnaires and stuff.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.22,0:20:18.15,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,You brought a name for a new work with you, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:19.01,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,This is no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.94,0:20:20.59,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,No good?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.08,0:20:25.16,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,While you were talking to us, I came up with a lot of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:27.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should redraw this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:29.45,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,And to be honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.45,0:20:31.66,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,from the shock of falling from first to third,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:33.75,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really in the mood to talk about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:37.04,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,But I told you over and over, third is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:39.42,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,If you get disheartened at something simple like that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:40.74,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,you won't be able to make it as a mangaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.04,0:20:45.74,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,Having said that, the early report was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:47.76,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.61,0:20:50.47,Main,Hattori,0000,0000,0000,,How about we end it here for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:52.28,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.47,0:20:58.88,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin... I want to try for something mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.92,0:21:03.33,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,To be popular in Jack... I think you have to be mainstream, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.94,0:21:07.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But we were told there's no point in us trying something mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.13,0:21:09.83,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should just do what we've been doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:12.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,That was the plan to win against Eiji in NEXT!.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:14.62,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.62,0:21:17.12,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Eiji got 503 votes out of 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.12,0:21:19.41,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,More than half the voters thought it was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.59,0:21:23.88,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,A manga that two out of ten people will definitely think is interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.41,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.42,0:21:29.80,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,If we throw out half the votes from the outset, there's no way we can win!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:36.46,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking about it when I saw Eiji's work, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:38.69,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,even for mainstream, it wasn't just the artwork that was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:40.94,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,You could sort of see the author through the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:43.09,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,It gave off a strong sense of uniqueness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:46.40,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I thought so, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.40,0:21:47.86,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,A kind of "How does he do this?" feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.49,0:21:51.74,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Shuujin, you're great at making settings,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.74,0:21:54.00,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,so if you make a simpler setting than what we've had so far
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:56.71,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,and use mainstream characters, I think we can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:22:00.88,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it must be mainstream!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:04.09,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Saikou...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:05.80,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,There are a bunch of people who do mainstream,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.80,0:22:07.76,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,so being number one is hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.76,0:22:10.64,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, doing cult is just running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.64,0:22:12.89,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,What we're aiming for is number one in Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.35,0:22:17.89,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Cult stories can't be number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.39,0:22:21.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start again from scratch!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:21.97,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:38.41,Main,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, throwing scraps of paper all over the place?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.91,0:22:40.08,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.12,0:22:41.92,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry, we have to pick it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.92,0:22:42.25,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Y–{\alpha&HFF&}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:43.79,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Y–Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.39,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,{Ending}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.45,0:24:18.06,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so this is where Jack is made?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:19.22,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,That's Niizuma Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.22,0:24:21.39,Main,Eiji,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be Ashirogi Muto?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.39,0:24:22.85,Main,Shuujin,0000,0000,0000,,You know who we are?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.94,0:24:25.06,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Battle and Copying
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.06,0:24:27.77,Main,Saikou,0000,0000,0000,,When you embrace your dreams, rivals appear.
